        <Row Tag="LOC_OPTIONS_GROUP_GEOGRAPHIC_LABELS">
            <Text>Geographic Labels</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_MOD_GEO_LABELS_DESCRIPTION">
            <Text>Paints Civ VI-style names on the map: continents, islands, and natural wonders. Toggle it with the "Geographic Names" checkbox next to Yields in the mini-map lens menu.</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_GEO_LABELS_TOGGLE">
            <Text>Geographic Names</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_GEO_LABELS_OPT_FLAT">
            <Text>Geographic Labels: follow the terrain</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_GEO_LABELS_OPT_FLAT_DESC">
            <Text>Lay geographic names flat on the map and rotate them to run along the land — following mountain ranges, coastlines, and deserts the way Civilization VI did — instead of upright labels that always face the camera. Turn the labels themselves on or off with the "Geographic Names" checkbox in the mini-map's Decorations list.</Text>
        </Row>
        <Row Tag="LOC_GEO_LABELS_VIS_DESC">
            <Text>Show or hide this category of geographic label. Applies live while the "Geographic Names" map layer is on.</Text>
        </Row>
